<p id="p2">Matt Corey has once again gathered indie developers to organize&nbsp;<a href="https://indieappsales.com" rel="noopener noreferrer">a huge sale today and tomorrow</a>. Corey, the maker of&nbsp;<a href="https://app.appdivvy.io/redirect/b2b-prime-day" rel="noopener noreferrer">Bills to Budget</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href="https://app.appdivvy.io/redirect/signals-prime-day" rel="noopener noreferrer">Signals</a>, has organized a collection of over 250 apps that will be offered at a discount through Wednesday. The list is too long to publish here, but it includes many apps we&rsquo;ve covered here on MacStories and on&nbsp;<a href="https://club.macstories.net/" rel="noopener noreferrer">Club MacStories</a>&nbsp;in the past, including:</p>
